oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Surgical tips for bovine surgeries
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Mulon, Pierre-Yves
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Laceration of the teats is a surgical emergency, and appropriate care should be provided as soon as possible to ensure the best prognosis for return to production. Wounds on the teat are always impressive for owners and caretakers; however, teat lacerations support an overall favorable prognosis in most cases.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 2019 Recent Graduate Proceedings; 7-8
